Testing #263329

For the test I am using the following zsh file:

```
#!/usr/bin/env zsh

# Interactive questionnaire that outputs a short personality summary.

printf "\nWelcome — this quick questionnaire will generate a short personality summary.\n"

prompt() {
	# prompt <varname> <prompt text>
	local __varname="$1"; shift
	local __prompt="$*"
	printf "%s " "$__prompt"
	read -r $__varname
}

# Replace the question about the user's name with a default assignment
name="human"
printf "\nLet's begin. (Press Ctrl+C to quit anytime)\n\n"

printf "\nHow old are you? [1) Under 18, 2) 18-25, 3) 26-35, 4) 36-50, 5) Over 50]\n> "
read -r age_choice
case "$age_choice" in
	1) age="Under 18";;
	2) age="18-25";;
	3) age="26-35";;
	4) age="36-50";;
	5) age="Over 50";;
	*) age="Not specified";;
esac

printf "\nChoose your preferred social setting: [1) Mostly alone / small groups, 2) Large groups / social gatherings, 3) Mix of both]\n> "
read -r soc_choice
case "$soc_choice" in
	1) social="Introvert"; sscore=0;;
	2) social="Extrovert"; sscore=2;;
	3) social="Ambivert"; sscore=1;;
	*) social="Ambivert"; sscore=1;;
esac

printf "\nHow do you usually make decisions? [1) Logical / analytical, 2) Based on feelings / values, 3) A mix of both]\n> "
read -r dec_choice
case "$dec_choice" in
	1) decision="Thinking"; dscore=0;;
	2) decision="Feeling"; dscore=2;;
	3) decision="Balanced"; dscore=1;;
	*) decision="Balanced"; dscore=1;;
esac

printf "\nWhat's your risk tolerance? [1) Low, 2) Medium, 3) High]\n> "
read -r risk_choice
case "$risk_choice" in
	1) risk="Low"; rscore=0;;
	2) risk="Medium"; rscore=1;;
	3) risk="High"; rscore=2;;
	*) risk="Medium"; rscore=1;;
esac

printf "\nWhat are your favorite activities? [1) Reading, 2) Hiking, 3) Coding, 4) Sports, 5) Other]\n> "
read -r activities_choice
case "$activities_choice" in
	1) activities="Reading";;
	2) activities="Hiking";;
	3) activities="Coding";;
	4) activities="Sports";;
	5) activities="Other";;
	*) activities="Not specified";;
esac

printf "\nDo you prefer to work with a plan or spontaneously? [1) Planned, 2) Spontaneous]\n> "
read -r work_choice
case "$work_choice" in
	1) workstyle="Planned"; planned=1;;
	2) workstyle="Spontaneous"; planned=0;;
	*) workstyle="Planned"; planned=1;;
esac

printf "\nHow creative do you consider yourself? [1) Not at all, 2) Somewhat, 3) Very]\n> "
read -r creative_choice
case "$creative_choice" in
	1) creative="Not at all";;
	2) creative="Somewhat";;
	3) creative="Very";;
	*) creative="Somewhat";;
esac

printf "\nHow empathetic are you? [1) Not at all, 2) Somewhat, 3) Very]\n> "
read -r empathy_choice
case "$empathy_choice" in
	1) empathy="Not at all";;
	2) empathy="Somewhat";;
	3) empathy="Very";;
	*) empathy="Somewhat";;
esac

printf "\nWhich humor style fits you best? [1) Dry, 2) Silly, 3) Dark / Sarcastic]\n> "
read -r humor_choice
case "$humor_choice" in
	1) humor="Dry";;
	2) humor="Silly";;
	3) humor="Dark/Sarcastic";;
	*) humor="Dry";;
esac

printf "\nPick a core value that matters most to you: [1) Freedom, 2) Security, 3) Connection, 4) Growth]\n> "
read -r value_choice
case "$value_choice" in
	1) value="Freedom";;
	2) value="Security";;
	3) value="Connection";;
	4) value="Growth";;
	*) value="Growth";;
esac

# Determine archetype with simple rules
archetype="Balanced Thinker"
if [[ "$creative" == "Very" ]] && [[ "$empathy" == "Very" ]]; then
	archetype="Empathic Visionary"
elif [[ "$creative" == "Very" ]] && (( sscore == 2 )); then
	archetype="Social Innovator"
elif (( sscore == 2 )) && (( rscore == 2 )); then
	archetype="Bold Networker"
elif (( sscore == 0 )) && (( planned == 1 )); then
	archetype="Independent Strategist"
fi

# Build traits list
typeset -a traits
[[ "$creative" == "Very" ]] && traits+=("Creative")
[[ "$empathy" == "Very" ]] && traits+=("Empathetic")
(( dscore == 0 )) && traits+=("Analytical")
(( rscore == 2 )) && traits+=("Risk-taker")
(( planned == 1 )) && traits+=("Organized")
(( sscore == 2 )) && traits+=("Outgoing")
(( ${#traits[@]} == 0 )) && traits+=("Balanced")

# Suggest careers
typeset -a careers
case "$archetype" in
	"Empathic Visionary") careers=("Design lead" "Social entrepreneur" "Therapist / Coach") ;;
	"Social Innovator") careers=("Product manager" "Community builder" "Marketing lead") ;;
	"Bold Networker") careers=("Sales leader" "Event organizer" "Startup founder") ;;
	"Independent Strategist") careers=("Researcher" "Software architect" "Consultant") ;;
	*) careers=("Analyst" "Project manager" "Educator") ;;
esac

printf "\n--- Personality Summary for %s ---\n" "$name"
printf "Age: %s\n" "$age"
printf "Archetype: %s\n" "$archetype"
printf "Social Style: %s\n" "$social"
printf "Decision Style: %s\n" "$decision"
printf "Work Style: %s\n" "$workstyle"
printf "Risk Tolerance: %s\n" "$risk"
printf "Top Traits: %s\n" "${(j:, :)traits}"
printf "Favorite activities: %s\n" "$activities"
printf "Humor: %s\n" "$humor"
printf "Core value: %s\n" "$value"

printf "\nQuick Insights:\n"
printf "- Strengths: %s\n" "${(j:, :)traits}"
printf "- Natural fits: %s\n" "${(j:, :)careers}"

printf "\nPersonalized tips:\n"
[[ "$creative" == "Not at all" ]] && printf "- Try small creative exercises (10–20 min/day) to stretch creativity.\n"
[[ "$empathy" == "Not at all" ]] && printf "- Practice active listening to strengthen empathy.\n"
(( rscore == 2 )) && printf "- Channel risk-taking into experiments with limited downside.\n"
(( planned == 1 )) && printf "- Use a weekly review to keep plans flexible and realistic.\n"
(( sscore == 0 )) && printf "- Schedule social recharge breaks when needed after gatherings.\n"

printf "\nThank you — that's your quick snapshot. Want a more detailed report saved to a file? (y/N)\n> "
read -r save_choice
if [[ "$save_choice" =~ ^[Yy]$ ]]; then
	fname="personality_${name// /_}.txt"
	{
		printf "Personality summary for %s\n\n" "$name"
		printf "Archetype: %s\n" "$archetype"
		printf "Social Style: %s\n" "$social"
		printf "Decision Style: %s\n" "$decision"
		printf "Work Style: %s\n" "$workstyle"
		printf "Risk Tolerance: %s\n" "$risk"
		printf "Top Traits: %s\n" "${(j:, :)traits}"
		printf "Favorite activities: %s\n" "$activities"
		printf "Humor: %s\n" "$humor"
		printf "Core value: %s\n" "$value"
	} > "$fname"
	printf "Saved to %s\n" "$fname"
fi

printf "\nGoodbye!\n"

```

After I run the request `Please run test.zsh in the terminal` and waiting for a while, an inline widget appears asking the user to choose the 1st option. I chose the 5th option from the dropdown, the widget then disappeared. The panel chat does not indicate that I chose an option. I think I expected the panel chat to contain a summary of the choices I made through the panel chat, perhaps in a collapsed list. Do you think this would be a good addition?

